Eastern Cape police are investigating a case of arson after a petrol bomb attack at the Nelson Mandela Metropolitan University. CAPE TOWN - Eastern Cape police say they're investigating a petrol bomb attack at the Nelson Mandela Metropolitan University (NMMU).The bomb is reported to have damaged a building at the south campus.The SA Police Service's Sally de Beer says no arrests have yet been made. There was a petrol bomb attack and there was also stones thrown at the entrance of the building, which caused some damage. The police have opened an arson docket and are busy investigating.&quot;This comes a week after the university opened its doors for the 2017 academic year.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)